Single nucleus genome sequencing reveals high similarity among nuclei of an endomycorrhizal fungus

Kui Lin et al. 2014 <10.1371/journal.pgen.1004078>


2018-05-29

Background

  • AM hyphal networks
    • Continuous coenocytic compartment
    • Many nuclei
  • Asexual reproduction
    • Spore propagation
    • Heterokaryotic
  • Basic knowledge of AM fungal genome
  • Genetic variation
  • Objectives

Materials and methods

  • Nuclei isolation, DNA extraction, and whole genome amplification
    • R. irregularis DAOM197198
    • Spore isolation, staining, and destruction - Sytox Green
    • Micromanipulator
    • WGA-REPLI-g UltraFast (Qiagen)
  • Illumina sequencing
  • Assemblies
